Here we are using the concept of longest-substring-without-repeating-characters
Link: https://leetcode.com/problems/longest-substring-without-repeating-characters/

Lets understand the approach with example:

"wordgoodgoodgoodbestword", 
words = ["word","good","best","word"]

We will store the word and its freq in a map, lets name the map as "contain".
contain[words[i]]++

Our map will look like:
word = 2
good = 1
best = 1

let len = length of words in words, ie len = words[0].length()

Then we will use two loops to iterate 
Outermost loop will determine the starting which is from 0 to  len - 1
Innermost loop will do a jump of i += len
and within this we will implement longest substring without repeating.

Lets try to visualise why we used two loop

s = "wordgoodgoodgoodbestword", 
words = ["word","good","best","word"]

We can break this as

word good good good best word 
or
w ordg oodg oodg oodb estw ord
or
wo rdgo odgo odgo odbe stwo rd
or
wor dgoo dgoo dgoo dbes twor d

if we further break it then it will be identical to the first 

Now after breaking, we just need to find the  longest substring without repeating-characters
But here our words may repeat as per the freq so instead of > 1 we will use > contain[word[i]] (contain is the map we made earlier) in our if condition.

