>All words share the same length, if we regard each word as a character,  we could apply the same idea as [Solution for 438. Find All Anagrams in a String](https://leetcode.com/problems/find-all-anagrams-in-a-string/discuss/175381/Beats-96-Sliding-Window-Java-with-Explanations).

>Current window `[i, j]` for `i`, `j` move `wordLength` characters per step.

>As long as window's length equals to `wordsTotalLength`, we validate current window.

>To cover all possible starting indices of concatenation, we should do LC438 for `wordLength` rounds. In each round, `i` starts at `round`.

****
```
    public List<Integer> findSubstring(String s, String[] words) {
        if (s == null || s.isEmpty() || words == null || words.length == 0) return new ArrayList<>();

        int wordLength = words[0].length(), wordsTotalLength = wordLength * words.length;
        List<Integer> startIndices = new ArrayList<>();

        // Map word to its frequency in words.
        Map<String, Integer> wordToFreqWords = new HashMap<>();
        for (String word : words) {
            wordToFreqWords.put(word, wordToFreqWords.getOrDefault(word, 0) + 1);
        }

        Map<String, Integer> wordToFreqWindow;

        for (int round = 0; round < wordLength; round++) {
            int j = round + wordLength - 1;
            wordToFreqWindow = new HashMap<>();
            for (int i = round; i + wordsTotalLength - 1 < s.length(); i += wordLength) {
                while (j - i + 1 <= wordsTotalLength) { 
                    String word = s.substring(j - wordLength + 1, j + 1);
                    wordToFreqWindow.put(word, wordToFreqWindow.getOrDefault(word, 0) + 1);
                    j += wordLength;
                }

                if (wordToFreqWindow.equals(wordToFreqWords)) startIndices.add(i);

                String word = s.substring(i, i + wordLength);
                wordToFreqWindow.put(word, wordToFreqWindow.getOrDefault(word, 0) - 1);
                if (wordToFreqWindow.get(word) == 0) wordToFreqWindow.remove(word);
            }
        }

        return startIndices;
    }
