	3.6. `if (ci, cj) in should_preserve: continue` - there is no need to double-process the cell if it's preserved
	3.7. if the cell is preserved - it can preserve the neighbor cell - call `preserve_connected`
4. Go through all the cells excluding borders and set them to 'X' if they are not preserved.


