    void dfs(vector<vector<char>>& board,int i,int j,int m,int n)
    {
        if(i<0 || i>= m || j<0 || j>=n || board[i][j] != 'O') return;
        board[i][j] = '$';
        dfs(board,i-1,j,m,n);
        dfs(board,i+1,j,m,n);
        dfs(board,i,j-1,m,n);
        dfs(board,i,j+1,m,n);
    }

solutions.content:
**Approach**
1. Iterate through the borders of the matrix that are marked as O
2. Take vertices from previous step and DFS across all neighbors marking O's with A's
3. Iterate through the entire matrix converting A's to O's and O's to X's.

**Initial State**
* The red background is a signal for O's connected to the border. The blue background is for O's not connected to the border.

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/aefc6c1c-50d9-4e02-99dc-d2422facf8ac_1636053458.1714075.png)


**Intermediate State**
* Mark all O's connected to the border as A's
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fd02d5ee-2a41-4d5e-8968-fbcdf27f5aec_1636051961.0175774.png)

**Final State**
* Convert O's to X's and A's to O's
![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/fcd6b201-859d-4f7c-b075-b52e8b7e3d26_1636051821.9669514.png)


**Code**
```
public void solve(char[][] board) {
        for (int i = 0; i < board.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < board[0].length; j++) {
                // is a border coordinate
                if ((i == 0 || i == board.length - 1 || j == 0 || j == board[0].length - 1) && board[i][j] == 'O') {
                    dfs(i, j, board);
                }
            }
        }

        for (int i = 0; i < board.length; i++) {
            for (int j = 0; j < board[0].length; j++) {
                if (board[i][j] == 'O') {
                    board[i][j] = 'X';
                } else if (board[i][j] == 'A') {
                    board[i][j] = 'O';
                }
            }
        }
    }

    void dfs(int i, int j, char[][] board) {
        board[i][j] = 'A';
        int[][] moves = new int[][]{{0, 1}, {0, -1}, {1, 0}, {-1, 0}};
        for (int[] move : moves) {
            int newI = i + move[0];
            int newJ = j + move[1];
            // is within bounds + equal to O
            if (newI >= 0 && newI < board.length && newJ >= 0 && newJ < board[0].length && board[newI][newJ] == 'O') {
                dfs(newI, newJ, board);
            }
        }
    }
```

**Time + Space**
N - # of rows
M - # of columns

Time Complexity: O(2(N * M)) ~ O (N * M), we are traversing the grid two times.
Space Complexity: O(N * M). The recursive stack in our DFS can grow to this size if the board is all O's.

