# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
In BST, Inorder travesal gives node's values in sorted order.
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
We'll store all values into a vector during inorder traversal, and return vec[k-1].

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(N)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(H)

# Code
