**Idea:** kth smallest element in a BST is the kth item in its inorder traversal because IOT of a BST gives the element in increasing order.
>**T/S:** O(h + k)/O(h), where h = height of BST
```
public int kthSmallest(TreeNode root, int k) {
	var kSmallest = new int[1];
	inorder(root, new int[]{k}, kSmallest);
	return kSmallest[0];
}

private void inorder(TreeNode root, int[] count, int[] kSmallest) {
	if (root == null || count[0] == 0)
		return;
	// recurse left
	inorder(root.left, count, kSmallest);
	// visit
	if (--count[0] == 0)
		kSmallest[0] = root.val;
	else
	// recurse right
		inorder(root.right, count, kSmallest);
}
```
