# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
An in-order traversal of a BST will always be in sorted ascending order. We just need to do an in-order traversal and keep counting values from the beginning till we reach the `kth`value. Then we can stop the traversal and return the obtained value.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(k)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(k)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
  int k;

  private int inOrder(TreeNode node) {
    if (node == null) return -1;

    var ans = inOrder(node.left);
    if (ans != -1 && --k <= 0) return ans;

    if (--k <= 0) return node.val;

    return inOrder(node.right);
  }

  public int kthSmallest(TreeNode root, int k) {
    this.k = k;
    return inOrder(root);
  }
}
```
