**Intuition**: Visit from the left nodes first. Keep track of number of nodes visited and last visited node. When the visited node count becomes k, don’t visit any other node.

**Algorithm**
Intitially we have lastVisitedNode = -1, visitedNodeCount = 0
1. If root == NULL then return
1. Visit left nodes recursively
1. If visitedNodeCount < k
	1. Visited current node by making lastVisitedNode = root → val
	1. visitedNodeCount++
	1. visited right subtree nodes recursively

**Code**
```
void kthSmallestHelper(TreeNode *root, int k, int &nodeVisitedCount, int &lastVisitedNode){
        if(root == NULL) return  ;
        kthSmallestHelper(root -> left, k, nodeVisitedCount, lastVisitedNode) ;

        if(nodeVisitedCount < k){
            lastVisitedNode = root -> val ;
            nodeVisitedCount++ ;
            kthSmallestHelper(root -> right, k, nodeVisitedCount, lastVisitedNode) ;
        }
    }

    int kthSmallest(TreeNode* root, int k) {
        int nodeVisitedCount = 0, lastVisitedNode = -1 ;
        kthSmallestHelper(root, k, nodeVisitedCount, lastVisitedNode) ;
        return lastVisitedNode ;
    }
