# 	Steps:
   Please upvote if you find it helpful .
	Every Interation we can have either of the three conditions:
	We keep interating unitll our **reach>=n**

	1. If my current number is less than or equal to reach, then add that to the reach and move i forward.
	2. If my current element, nums[i] is greater than the current reach then we search for the smallest number we should add to make the current element in reach, which is going to be  (reach+1).
	3. If we surpass the array boundary i.e. i>nums.size(), we are again going to look for the smallest element we can add to reach the desired target n. This smallest number is going to be again (reach+1).
```
class Solution {
public:
    int minPatches(vector<int>& nums, int n) {
        int count=0;
        long long reach=0;
        int i=0;
        while(reach<n){
            if(i>=nums.size()){
                reach+=reach+1;
                count++;
            }
            else if(i<nums.size() && nums[i]<=reach+1){
                reach+=nums[i];
                i++;
            }
            else {
                reach+=reach+1;
                count++;
            }
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```

